FROM debian:bullseye-slim

WORKDIR /var/www

# Software package layer
# Nodesource setup comes after yarnpkg because it runs `apt-get update`
RUN apt-get update \
    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        apt-transport-https \
        build-essential \
        ca-certificates \
        curl \
        gnupg2 \
    && curl -f -sL https://packages.sury.org/php/apt.gpg | apt-key add - \
    && echo "deb https://packages.sury.org/php/ bullseye main" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/php.list \
    && apt-get update \
    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        cron \
        make \
        nginx \
        netcat \
        php8.1 \
        php8.1-cli \
        php8.1-curl \
        php8.1-fpm \
        php8.1-gd \
        php8.1-mbstring \
        php8.1-memcached \
        php8.1-mysql \
        php8.1-pgsql \
        php8.1-xml \
        php8.1-zip \
        php-apcu \
        php-dev \
        php-bcmath \

EXPOSE 34000/tcp
